history.content: By definition, being on the waitlist means you are not guaranteed to be enrolled. It may very well work out but you can't count on it.  We have no way of knowing how many already declared majors will sign up in phase 2, for example.

I don't think you'll get skipped on the waitlist until your position is single-digit, so I guess you can drop 61C when your position becomes < 10.

Also, I personally feel that both those classes will necessarily need to expand for you to get in, given your waitlist positions..

I’m a sophomore taking 70 rn, so I’m not declared yet. I’m on the waitlist for 170 and 188 (positions 184 and 277, respectively). Am I basically guaranteed to get into them? I’m asking because I’m enrolled in 61C for next semester as a backup plan in case I don’t get into 170, but on the other hand I don’t want to get skipped on the 170 waitlist when waitlists are processed because of the time conflict with 61C. What should I do? I don’t want to drop 61C now and then end up not getting into 170 and/or 188...
history.subject: Getting Into 170 and 188
